    "body": "@caybro I tried every possible combination to handle that. Also tried adding layout fill and alignments to icon itself etc etc.\r\n\r\nIt is just Qt Layout issue. In theory setting Qt.AlignRight to icon and Qt.AlignLeft to text should align them, but isn't doing it for some reason.\r\nAlso setting Layout.fillWidth: true for both doesn't split size by half.\r\n \r\nCurrently nearly all places use small buttons where this solution is fine, but should be able to handle centering for stretched buttons.",
